diff:1616292127:1616292127:=1,69d0%0a%3c (:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c [[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a%3c [[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !Philosophy Lessons from PLAY%0a%3c %0a%3c :Author: AnanyaV%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Summary:''' \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Polysemy of the word "play"%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c When you are young, you PLAY outside with your friends, and PLAY pranks on them. You also PLAY board games like Monopoly, and you might not always PLAY fair or PLAY by the rules. When you take part in a sport, you PLAY that sport, and in competitive sports, you PLAY against teams. In the theatre, you watch a PLAY, where actors PLAY characters. If you like music, you might PLAY music on your phone, or you might learn to PLAY an instrument. When you are in a stressful situation, you try to PLAY it cool, and if you are running out of time, you might PLAY for time. Sometimes, you avoid risks and PLAY it safe. If you want to make something happen, you bring it into PLAY.%0a%3c %0a%3c In the language of the Nacirema, “play” is often attributed to areas that the Nacirema people view as leisurely, being used within the contexts of games, music, sports, and theatre. However, there are some exceptions to this as we have seen in the latter examples, with “play” being used to describe how one might react to a situation. These contextual differences in the use of “play” showcase the linguistic peculiarities of the Nacirema culture.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: LanguageOfTheNacirema:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
